                <note rend="inline" type="source">761.9415 Amur River/3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-07-01T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >July 1, 1937—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 1—8:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>196. Reference Embassy’s 195, July 1, 3 p.m. Following telegram has been received
                    from the Consul General at Harbin.</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“July 1, 11 a.m. The Foreign Commissioner confirms press reports that
                        yesterday a Russian gunboat was sunk by gun fire during an engagement
                        following an alleged invasion of Manchukuo waters in the Amur River south of
                        Taheiho.”</p>
                    <p>“The Consulate General feels that the new epidemic of border incidents is
                        inspired by the Japanese Army and indicates that the Japanese Army really
                        believes that the recent executions of military officers in Soviet Russia
                        reveal hitherto unsuspected Soviet military weakness, although Japanese Army
                        officers have published the opinion that the Soviet Army was strengthened by
                        those executions”.</p>
                </quote>
                <p>By mail to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
